SIMPLE: internode
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Internode
<hw>In"ter*node`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>internodium</ets>; <ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>nodus</ets>
knot.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The space between two nodes or
points of the stem from which the leaves properly arise.</def>
<rj><au>H. Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A part between two joints; a
segment; specifically, one of the phalanges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internodial</ent>⟦br⟧
